They sort of do a little of everything, but unfortunately everything isn’t done spectacularly well. It’s still satisfying enough to come here for a meal, but most items have a better alternative. I will give them credit for having a pretty decent clay pot rice in Brooklyn and I’ve yet to have better, but there’s improvement to be desired. They’re stingy with the toppings for the rice and have absolutely no vegetables for most of them, if i recall correctly. I’ve also had bones in the salted fish one, so that’s a bit disappointing. Theres very little grilled rice at the bottom, which is one of my favorite parts.  It is pretty cool how they do delivery and take out for the pot, Ill credit them there. You can nab a worn but usable pot for like two bucks and make your own.  There’s no springiness to the rice noodles. The char siu and roast pork are pretty good, but quality is inconsistent. Overall, decent place.

I didnt sit down to eat.  I got takeout.  I only got rice cake with 3 sauces on it.  It had 4 rice cakes.  I saw a picture of it on the restaurant's window as I was walking by.  Inside was very busy.  There were a couple of deliveries, and a lot of takeout orders.  I took a menu because a lot of there food looked interesting and delicious. So when I go into Brooklyn again I will definitely sit at a table and order more food.  I'm not sure if 5 stars was suitable right now until I've tasted more variety of their food, but I'm confident enough to know that it will be delicious and would deserve a 5 star rating.

MUST READ FIRST!!!!  Ok...so here goes. I had to do this. This was my first time coming here. My wife's friend suggested this place for having great tasting food. To be honest, I never got to taste the food and this is why....When you walk into this establishment, you are welcomed with a great smell of different foods but that as far as my compliments will go.  In the entrance they have a cashier and a small cutting station where they have duck, pork, and  chicken hanging on racks. And only two cutting blocks (one of which they only use). They cut all kinds of meats including fish, octopus and anything you can think of on this one cutting block with the same meat cleaver. The worker was handling all of the meat like an assembly line. There were so many different types of juices and greases caked all over the place, so if you order duck, you best believe that you are eating fish, chicken, beef, pork, octopus and anything else you can think of.  Underneath the racks of various meats, there is a sink that collects all of the greases and fats that fall off these meats. This sink was not only full of these greases and fats, but also had racks of ribs and other meats floating in it. This meat that was floating in the sink was also being served to hungry patrons. I also observed woman that was cutting up the food wiping her nose and scratching herself with the gloves on and you guessed it, continued cutting up the food.  The entire front area where this practice was happening was also outright filthy. So much dust everywhere. The air conditioning unit looks as if you can knit a sweater with all of the dust that was caked onto it. I can only imagine how much dust and bacteria would blow onto the racks of meat whenever it is turned on. If the front area looks like this, then I can only imagine what they're doing in the main kitchen.  The employees do not practice anything sanitary. Food, trash, and even money is handled without even changing gloves. Wow.  Overall, my experience there was so bad that I had rushed home and had a horrible New Year experience in my own restroom and I didn't even eat the food. Please beware. If you're into risking things for an adrenaline rush then this is the place for you. Otherwise, beware. I truly hope that the owners read this and upgrade their practices.  MY GOD....HOW DID THEY HAVE AN "A" RATING

Food: 4/5 Staff: 1/5 Variety: 3/5 Uniqueness as compared to other places in the area: 1/5 not very unique.  Went to this restaurant at this location a total of three times. First two times it was eat-in, the food was a bit oily but still edible. Nevertheless it is still tasty. Compared to the other restaurants in the area, this place isn't unique at all. The variety of dishes it offers is quite average. The third time I came here is to get take out for the ready-made meats hanging by the front. I got roast pig.  Normally, they would weigh it and display it to both the customer and themselves for pricing. This place hides the number so only they could see it. That's a little too dishonest for my taste. I rather other places that would show me the actual price for the meat I pay for. That is why it is staff 1/5.  I recommend solely ordering food made in the kitchen.

The prices are great. And the food tastes so fresh. I usually come here for a quick and easy dinner with my parents. I usually get the 3 meat over rice.
